@startuml channel-health-reduction
' How the AgentChannelReconciler reduces per-replica health states into PlatformConnected.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/user/platform-adapters.md
!include _style.puml

start
:AgentChannelReconciler fans out
**GET /v1/channels/health** to every gateway Pod IP;
:Skip unreachable replicas;
:Collect, per reachable replica:
**{ state, replicaStartedAt }**
state in { success, failure, empty };

if (**Rule 1**: any reachable replica reports **success**?) then (yes)
  :**PlatformConnected = True**
  reason = WebhookReady
  + the **most recent** success's metadata;
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (**Rule 2**: any reachable replica reports **failure**?) then (yes)
  :**PlatformConnected = False**
  reason + lastError from the **most recent** failure:
  WebhookAuthFailed | AgentNotReady | DispatchFailed
  | CallbackInvalid | CallbackRejected;
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (**Rule 3**: at least one replica up for the **full window**\n(gateway.channelHealthWindow, default 5m)\n**AND** every reachable replica reports **empty**?) then (yes)
  :**PlatformConnected = Unknown**
  reason = NoRecentTraffic;
  note right
    **Both halves are required.**
    A replica with now - replicaStartedAt < window
    has not been alive long enough to observe a
    full window. Its **empty** is not evidence that
    the channel is silent, only that this replica
    cannot prove silence.
  end note
  stop
else (no)
endif

:**Rule 4**: **preserve the existing condition**
(write nothing);
note right #FFE4B5
  A deliberate no-op, not a gap. Reached when no
  replica has full-window coverage and no in-window
  observation exists anywhere.
  ....
  **This is also the all-replicas-unreachable path.**
  Writing a state here would flap the condition on
  every coordinated gateway restart.
end note
stop
@enduml
